<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,151,860]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,289,763,788]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Biology</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[304,565,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Meteorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acerbiavorus">
<emphasis box="[304,565,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Meteorus acerbiavorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from specimens reared from cocoons of the arctiid moth 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Quensel" baseAuthorityYear="1802" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Arctiidae" genus="Acerbia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="alpina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Acerbia alpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected in June in nothern 
<collectingCountry box="[606,692,799,823]" name="Finland" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Finland</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stigenberg, J. &amp; Vikberg, V. &amp; Belokobylskij, S. A." box="[708,966,799,823]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="21 - 24" refId="ref59841" refString="Stigenberg, J., Vikberg, V. &amp; Belokobylskij, S. A. (2011) Meteorus acerbiavorus sp. nov. (Hymenoptera, Braconidae), a gregarious parasitoid of Acerbia alpina (Quensel) (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae) in North Finland. Journal of Natural History, 45, (21 - 24), 1275 - 1294." type="journal article" year="2011">Stigenberg et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). It is gregarious and 39 to 98 parasitoid cocoons have been found in a single host cocoon.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
